events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — With Giannis Antetokounmpo in peak form since returning from COVID-19 protocols, the red-hot Milwaukee Bucks are scoring at their highest rate of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis' triple-double leads Milwaukee to 6th straight win

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Saddiq Bey hit a 3-pointer with 1.9 seconds left in overtime and finished with 21 points, leading the Detroit Pistons to a 117-116 win over the San Antonio Spurs on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bey hits 3-pointer late in OT, Pistons edge Spurs 117-116

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer for the second straight game to give the Chicago Bulls a 120-119 win over the Washington Wizards on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan beats the buzzer again, giving Bulls 7 straight wins

headlines.description: — The Los Angeles Clippers came to Brooklyn without their coach and many of their best players.
headlines.shortLinkText: Short-handed Clippers rally to beat Nets 120-116

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 24 points and Facundo Campazzo added a career-high 22 as the Denver Nuggets used a huge second quarter to take control in a 124-111 win over the Houston Rockets on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Campazzo help Nuggets to 124-111 rout of Rockets

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Earning road victories against other top NBA teams is quickly becoming a habit for Golden State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors rally in the 4th quarter for 123-116 win over Jazz
